Description. Based on 11 wholemounts and 2 sets of serial sections. Measurements and ratios in Table 1 . Body small, oval to fusiform, widest at level of ventral sucker (
Fig. 3
). Tegument unarmed, but thrown into numerous denticulate annular folds. Oral sucker shallow cup-shaped, almost terminal. Ventral sucker rounded, larger than oral sucker, just pre-equatorial. Prepharynx short. Pharynx oval. Oesophagus long, thin-walled. Intestinal bifurcation dorsal to ventral sucker. Caeca blind, divergent, narrow, reaching just into hindbody or just to testis.
